Mangrove trees are tolerant to high levels of heavy metals (
MacFarlane et al., 2007
). Specially 

Avicennia
species

exhibit greater tolerance and have accumulative properties to numerous metals than other mangrove species (
MacFarlane and Burchett, 2002
; 
Soepadmo et al., 1984
).

